to the point of wholesale elimination.<EOS> It would be really strange for Congress
to say you can eliminate obligations altogether or tweak them just the littlest
bit, but you can't do anything in between.<EOS> 

Well, but it's "waive "particular regulatory or statutory provisions.<EOS> 

That's right.<EOS> 

That to me suggests a much more focused use of the word.<EOS> 

Well, it's "waive or modify" paired with the authority to do that with respect
